entries.femaleVariant: Hey! I know you! We had a deal!
Hey, Ken. Is it time for the next episode "Daddy-Daughter Dilemmas?"
Sit. I'll tell you the rest.
[Sit by Ken.]
And she had just called me... a few days before. If only I'd answered...
OK.
Fuck... OK. I mean, no one should die alone.
What, suddenly realize your priorities ruined your life? No, this is on you. Don't drag me into it.
Don't rope me into this.
Thank you... But can we do it elsewhere? I have a place.
Yes.
No.
All right.
Maybe later.
Yeah, sure.
Can't right now. In a bit of a hurry.
And you just had to know everything about me... Had you pegged for a flake.
I'm back. Not hurryin' off anywhere else for now.
You're just lucky no one took your spot. Have a seat.
I'm back.
You, come here!
Last time, I...I wasn't quite myself. It's starting to happen more often... But that's neither here nor there.
Our first conversation made me realize a few things. Strange as it sounds, I want to thank you for being nosy.
I'd give it all just to hear her raise her voice again.
I'll be back. Maybe.
I'll still be here. Maybe.
Enid, my baby girl...
You deserved it.
I'm sorry.
Tell me in the car.
Happy to be of service.
Got a quick tongue, don't you? Just like my Enid... You know, there was a time I thought she was incapable of using a normal tone.
Enid's dead, isn't she?
Why'd you bite my head off before?
Why'd you bite my head off before?
Look, you and Enid... You remind me a lot of her.
I fooled myself into thinking if you gave me any words of sympathy, forgiveness, it'd be like it came from her.
Noticed a lot past tense before. She...she's dead, isn't she?
She called me right after she signed her contract. Explained to me that Biotechnica had the DNA for extinct animals she wanted to resurrect.
"Platypuses, dad! Platypuses and axolotls! You know I've dreamed of this since elementary school! Ever since you got me that book."
I said...I said never wanted to see her again. And hung up.
You're a dick.
I understand... in a way.
Dick move, but I understand the instinct. She knew she picked the enemy over you.
Thanks for the reminder all corpos are massive dickheads.
I broke off contact, not wanting to know what she did, where she lived. She betrayed the company... and, by extension, me.
I know...I know! I was just so furious, I lost myself... How could I know it would be the last time I'd hear her voice?
That call still haunts my sleep... How could I know it would be the last time I'd hear her voice?
Whoever isn't with us is against us... Classic.
Don't you mock me. Not right now.
Then, one day the CEO called me in to talk. I thought he wanted to talk strategy for the upcoming quarter...
But as soon as I stepped in, he told me he had Enid  killed.
Why do it, have her killed?
Competition? To test my loyalty, maybe?
Enid focused on artificial tissues, regenerative work... heart muscle.
If Biotechnica took it to market, Kendachi pacemaker sales... they would have plummeted.
Jesus, Ken, I'm sorry... You fucked up, but not enough to deserve this.
Don't know what you expected after sellin' yourself to a corp. One day you're destroying lives, next it's yours. Circle of life.
Why have Enid killed?
Your words won't change anything. Still... thank you. I mean it.
I didn't deserve that. I did everything for her! Everything!
You really so fuckin' certain?
Guessin' we're at the part we agreed on. What is it you want from me for your story? Revenge?
I would've killed him.
I'd have gutted the bastard. Dont' care if his security flatlined me after.
When the initial shock passed, I thought of nothing else. I had to wipe that arrogant smirk from his face.
So I threw myself at him in a rage. If only I had mantis blades instead of my bare hands...
Finally, a good decision. Only a shame it came too late.
They didn't kill me, though. Would've been a bad PR move. Instead they waited – waited until I wound up here.
Just... kill me. That's it.
I have no strength left, and I don't want it back. I don't even have enough to pull the trigger.
Wait, please! You can't leave me like this now!
No? Watch me.
Last one had quite the dramatic conclusion.
[Offer Ken a cigarette.]
I don't smoke.
Here. To cool your nerves?
Out of luck. Don't smoke.
Got a cigarette? It's a perfect day for a puff.
For our history lesson.
New day, new disappointments... It's fine.
